Consider the following graph woith a quoted label:

```
digraph G {
    a [label="Graph with quoted dash \"-\" string"];
}
```

it should look like this:

![rendered version](http://g.gravizo.com/g?
digraph G {
    a [label="Graph with quoted dash \"-\" string"];
})

However, dot_parser doesn't recognize it, producing

> pyparsing.ParseException: Expected "}" (at char 18), (line:2, col:7)

```
Why not to allow  node names with compass points? I've tested it with 'dot' 
binary (version 2.26.3) and it works. Compass points are useful when generating 
network charts.

------ dotfile.dot ------
digraph G {
"00:14";
"Node B";
"00:14" -> "Node B";
"Node B" -> "00:14";
}
------ dotfile.dot ------

$ dot -o output.png dotfile.dot -Tpng
$ dot -V
dot - graphviz version 2.26.3 (20100126.1600)

Thank you for this project.
Greetings
```

